there doesn=E2=80=99t seem to be much precedent on how movie rights square =
with the so-called =E2=80=9CDickens provision=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94the automati=
c 25-year authorial rights reversion inspired by a penniless-when-he-died <=
strong>Charles Dickens</strong>, which is now written into copyright law ev=
erywhere from Ireland to South Africa. While there may be reasons=E2=80=94<=
em>e.g.</em>, Canada only recently extended its copyright term from 50 to 7=
0 years, altering the cost-benefit analysis of pursuing reversionary rights=
=E2=80=94the
unprecedented nature of the situation indicates that this probably won=E2=
=80=99t be an easy or straightforward case. Frankly, that=E2=80=99d be so e=
ven if the Superman rights didn=E2=80=99t already have a complicated legal =
backstory.=C2=A0</p></div>
