argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Back in 1938, Shuster and his writing partner, =
<strong>Jerry
Siegel</strong>, without the benefit of legal counsel, sold the rights to t=
heir fledgling superhero to Detective Comics for $130. Shortly thereafter, =
<em>Action Comics </em>No. 1 rocketed Superman into the cultural stratosphe=
